# Bubble Trouble RL — Full PPO Training Pipeline

Complete workflow from human demos through pretraining, RL training, and
post-training optimization. Each step builds on the previous.

## Prerequisites

```bash
python -m venv .venv && source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

---

## Phase 1: Demonstration Recording

Record near-perfect human play for behavioral cloning. The scrubber UI lets
you rewind and retry sections for clean recordings.

```bash
# Record demos level-by-level
python src/record_demos.py               # start from level 1
python src/record_demos.py 5             # start from level 5

# Combine separate session files into one
python src/combine_demos.py checkpoints/user_warmups/demo_*.npz

# Preview without writing
python src/combine_demos.py checkpoints/user_warmups/demo_*.npz --dry-run
```

Output: `checkpoints/user_warmups/demo_TIMESTAMP.npz`
Format: observations (T,968), actions (T,2), level_ids (T,), rewards (T,)

---

## Phase 2: Behavioral Cloning Pretraining

Train the policy architecture via supervised learning on recorded demos.
Two-phase: actor BC (weighted cross-entropy) then value function (MC returns).

```bash
python src/pretrain_bc.py checkpoints/user_warmups/demo_*.npz
```

Options:
```bash
python src/pretrain_bc.py demos/*.npz --max-epochs 200 --lr 5e-4
python src/pretrain_bc.py demos/*.npz --no-value    # skip value pretraining
```

Output: `checkpoints/user_warmups/bc_pretrained.zip`

---

## Phase 3: PPO Training

### Option A: MaskablePPO (primary — action-masked, feedforward)

```bash
# Full run with BC warm start + DAPG demo regularization + foresight rewards
python src/train_ppo.py \
    --warmup checkpoints/user_warmups/bc_pretrained.zip \
    --demo checkpoints/user_warmups/demo_*.npz \
    --foresight

# Full run from scratch (no demos)
python src/train_ppo.py

# Quick smoke test
python src/train_ppo.py --timesteps 100000 --n-envs 4

# Resume from checkpoint
python src/train_ppo.py \
    --resume checkpoints/ppo/periodic/ppo_50000000_steps.zip \
    --vecnorm checkpoints/ppo/periodic/ppo_50000000_steps_vecnorm.pkl
```

Key flags:
- `--warmup`: Load BC-pretrained weights. Uses compressed WARMUP_CURRICULUM,
  10x lower LR, PolicyAnchorCallback to prevent forgetting.
- `--demo`: Enable DAPG — decaying BC auxiliary loss alongside PPO. Level-
  stratified sampling matches current curriculum phase.
- `--foresight`: Simulate 120 frames forward after ball hits to reward shots
  that produce ceiling pop chains. Only activates on levels 9+.
- `--n-envs N`: Parallel workers (default: 80). Can exceed core count since
  workers are mostly blocked on IPC.
- `--device cpu|cuda|mps`: CPU is fastest for this network size.

### Option B: RecurrentPPO (LSTM — temporal reasoning)

```bash
# Full run with BC warm start + foresight rewards
python src/train_recurrent.py \
    --warmup checkpoints/user_warmups/bc_pretrained.zip \
    --foresight

# Quick smoke test
python src/train_recurrent.py --timesteps 100000 --n-envs 4
```

Note: RecurrentPPO loads only the features extractor from BC (not the full
policy). No action masking — the LSTM learns to avoid invalid shots via the
can_fire observation and wasted_shot penalty. No DAPG (LSTM hidden states
aren't available in demo data).

### Training outputs

```
checkpoints/ppo/
  best/best_model.zip                    # best eval reward
  best/best_model_vecnorm.pkl            # matching VecNormalize stats
  periodic/ppo_50000000_steps.zip        # periodic snapshots
  periodic/ppo_50000000_steps_vecnorm.pkl
  final_model.zip                        # end of training
  final_model_vecnorm.pkl
```

### Monitoring

```bash
tensorboard --logdir ./logs
```

Key metrics: `game/levels_cleared`, `game/episode_reward`, `game/ceiling_pops`,
`eval/mean_reward`, `bc_aux/shoot_recall`, `kl_anchor/loss`

---

## Phase 4: Post-Training Optimization

These steps boost performance on hard levels (9-12) using the trained
checkpoint — no retraining of the base model required.

### 4a. MCTS Inference (search-augmented play)

Run Monte Carlo Tree Search at inference time. The trained policy provides
action priors; MCTS simulates consequences to find better actions.

```bash
# Visual evaluation with MCTS
python src/mcts_play.py checkpoints/ppo/best/best_model.zip

# Headless with more simulations for maximum performance
python src/mcts_play.py checkpoints/ppo/best/best_model.zip \
    --no-render --episodes 50 --n-simulations 120 --horizon 180

# With VecNormalize stats
python src/mcts_play.py model.zip --vec-normalize model_vecnorm.pkl
```

Options:
- `--n-simulations N`: MCTS rollouts per decision (default 60, more = better but slower)
- `--horizon N`: Rollout depth in frames (default 120 = 2 seconds)
- `--decision-interval N`: Run MCTS every N frames (default 6 = ~10 decisions/sec)
- `--c-puct F`: Exploration constant (default 2.0)

### 4b. Self-Imitation Learning

Run the agent on hard levels, collect rare successful trajectories, add
them to the DAPG demo pool for retraining.

```bash
# Collect successful episodes on levels 9-12
python src/self_imitate.py checkpoints/ppo/best/best_model.zip \
    --start-level 9 --episodes 5000

# Use MCTS for higher-quality collection
python src/self_imitate.py checkpoints/ppo/best/best_model.zip \
    --start-level 9 --episodes 1000 --mcts --mcts-sims 60

# Lower the success threshold
python src/self_imitate.py model.zip --min-levels-cleared 1
```

Output: `checkpoints/self_imitation/self_imitation_L9_TIMESTAMP.npz`

Then retrain with the enriched demo pool:
```bash
python src/train_ppo.py \
    --warmup checkpoints/user_warmups/bc_pretrained.zip \
    --demo checkpoints/user_warmups/demo_*.npz \
           checkpoints/self_imitation/self_imitation_*.npz \
    --foresight
```

### 4c. GAIL Reward Shaping

Train a discriminator to distinguish expert play from agent play, then use
it as a dense reward bonus during PPO training.

```bash
# Step 1: Train discriminator on expert demos for levels 9-12
python src/gail.py train checkpoints/user_warmups/demo_*.npz \
    --min-level 9 --epochs 100

# Step 2: Use during training (requires code integration — see gail.py
# GAILRewardWrapper and GAILCallback for API)
```

Output: `checkpoints/gail/discriminator.pt`

### 4d. Specialist Composition

Train a separate specialist model for hard levels, compose at inference:

```bash
# Train specialist on levels 9-12 only
python src/train_ppo.py \
    --warmup checkpoints/user_warmups/bc_pretrained.zip \
    --demo checkpoints/user_warmups/demo_*.npz \
    --foresight \
    --checkpoint-dir checkpoints/ppo_specialist

# Evaluate with generalist + specialist composition
python src/evaluate.py play checkpoints/ppo/best/best_model.zip \
    --specialist checkpoints/ppo_specialist/best/best_model.zip \
    --specialist-level 9
```

---

## Evaluation

```bash
# Watch agent play (visual)
python src/evaluate.py play checkpoints/ppo/best/best_model.zip

# Headless stats over many episodes
python src/evaluate.py play checkpoints/ppo/best/best_model.zip \
    --no-render --episodes 100

# With VecNormalize stats from training
python src/evaluate.py play model.zip --vec-normalize model_vecnorm.pkl

# Benchmark raw env speed
python src/evaluate.py benchmark
```

---

## Human Play

```bash
python src/play.py          # start from level 1
python src/play.py 15       # start from level 15
```

Controls: arrow keys to move, space to shoot, R to restart, Q to quit.

---

## Recommended Full Pipeline

For best results, run these steps in order:

```bash
# 1. Record demos across all 12 levels (focus on levels 9-12)
python src/record_demos.py

# 2. Combine if recorded in multiple sessions
python src/combine_demos.py checkpoints/user_warmups/demo_*.npz

# 3. BC pretrain
python src/pretrain_bc.py checkpoints/user_warmups/demo_*.npz

# 4. Train PPO with all augmentations
python src/train_ppo.py \
    --warmup checkpoints/user_warmups/bc_pretrained.zip \
    --demo checkpoints/user_warmups/demo_*.npz \
    --foresight

# 5. Collect self-imitation data from best checkpoint
python src/self_imitate.py checkpoints/ppo/best/best_model.zip \
    --start-level 9 --episodes 5000 --mcts

# 6. Retrain with enriched demos
python src/train_ppo.py \
    --warmup checkpoints/user_warmups/bc_pretrained.zip \
    --demo checkpoints/user_warmups/demo_*.npz \
           checkpoints/self_imitation/self_imitation_*.npz \
    --foresight

# 7. Evaluate with MCTS for maximum performance
python src/mcts_play.py checkpoints/ppo/best/best_model.zip \
    --no-render --episodes 100 --n-simulations 120
```
